       Vangard Note...

            We first   heard   about  Sonic  Bloom  at  a  Global  Sciences
            Conference in Denver several  years  ago as well as through the
            excellent eco-paper, ACRES. USA.

            A loose  description of what it is and how it  came  to  be...a
            farmer noticed  that plants grew best in the morning especially
            when dew  formed  on the plants.   Also  coincident  with  high
            growth rates was the chirping of various birds as the sun rose.

            The farmer got the idea that the birdsong might  have something
            to do  with  the  growth  rate,  so  recorded various bird song
            patterns and  played  them  back  to  plants  in  a  controlled
            environment.  The  results  were  so  remarkable   that   other
            frequencies were  tried  which  led  to  ranges  of sound which
            greatly assisted  the  growth   of  plants.   The  addition  of
            fertilizer rich  moisture during this time further  accelerated
            the growth rates.

